g.text: The digital spreadsheet on the laptop screen is another object.
The spreadsheet can have two headers.
The laptop may be powered on or off.
The spreadsheet can merge or split cells.
The laptop is an instance of the class "Laptop".
The spreadsheet is an instance of the class "LaptopApps".
The colour of the laptop can be a field called "laptopColour"
The number of headers represented by a field called "numHeaders"
The ability to power on or off can be defined in a method called "onOffButton()"
The ability to merge or split cells can be defined in a method called "mergeSplitCells()"
